Revision history for DBIx-DataModel-Plugin-CDC

2.00  2026-04-04
    - Event emitter API: ->on(), ->log_to_dbi(), ->log_to_stderr().
      No handler classes — listeners are coderefs with metadata.
    - capture_old option (default: off) for lightweight CDC.
      Skips pre-fetch SELECT on class-method update/delete.
    - row_id always present in event envelope — identifies which row
      changed even when old_data is not captured.
    - primary_key in event envelope — lists PK column names.
    - Lightweight PK-only SELECT for class-method ops when capture_old=0.
    - Three modules total: CDC.pm, Table.pm, Event.pm.

1.01  2026-04-03
    - Initial implementation.
    - CDC::Table — table_parent class for insert/update/delete capture.
    - CDC::Event — event envelope with time-based IDs, changed_columns.
    - Transaction safety: mini-transaction wrapping, TOCTOU protection.
    - Follows DBIx::DataModel conventions: namespace::clean, croak.
